, tweets, and 24-hour news cycles is not as distinctive as we may believe. With rich end matter that includes the lyrics of poems and songs as well as a link to a superb recording of some of the songs by cabaret artist Helene Delavault, this interdisciplinary piece is highly recommended for serious students across the humanities as well as readers with an interest in 18th-century French culture and politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCommunication in politicszFrancezParisxHistoryy18th century. 0aInformation networkszFrancezParisxHistoryy18th century. 0aPolicezFrancezParisxHistoryy18th century. 0aPolitical activistszFrancezParisxHistoryy18th century. 0aPolitical culturezFrancezParisxHistoryy18th century. 0aPolitical poetry, FrenchxHistory and criticism. 0aStreet musiczFrancezParisxHistory and criticism. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221240uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674059276zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674059276423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674059276/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK